Cyfrowy Polsat, Ipopema, PZU: Central European Equity Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 
2011-03-15T23:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/cyfrowy-polsat-ipopema-pzu-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in central
European markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names. Share prices are from the last close.    Poland ’s WIG20 Index fell 0.3 percent and the Czech PX
Index dropped 0.1 percent. Hungary’s stock exchange was closed
for a public holiday.    Cyfrowy Polsat SA (CPS)  : Poland’s biggest satellite
television broadcaster will hold a news conference in Warsaw on
its Internet services. Cyfrowy added 2.2 percent to 15.68 zloty.    Ipopema Securities SA (IPE)  : Poland’s biggest non-bank
brokerage signed an agreement to buy all of Credit Suisse Asset
Management Polska SA, it said in a regulatory statement. Ipopema
fell 4.2 percent to 15 zloty.  PZU SA (PZU PW): Poland’s biggest insurer is scheduled to
report 2010 earnings. PZU shares fell 0.3 percent to 341.9
zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
